From 4757a3d3d80c3568b3bf7b4b4ece7f22cc24f401 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jesse <jbeck1689@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sun, 8 Mar 2026 20:46:22 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] Phase 3: Security hardening, rate limiting,
 accessibility, LLM stub

- Security headers in next.config (CSP, HSTS, X-Frame-Options, etc.)
- output: standalone for Docker/Cloud Run deployment
- Rate limiting: global (100/min per IP), login (5/min per email), registration (10/hr per IP), submissions (30/min per user)
- Enrollment verification on submit and complete routes
- Zod validation and 10KB size limit on submit payloads
- Structured logger module (pino-compatible interface)
- Accessibility: ARIA on progress bars, radiogroup on MC options, aria-live feedback, focus management on step nav, skip-to-content link
- LLM evaluator stub with full interface contract
- LlmConfig and StepMetadata validation schemas
